author: sussman
msg: Fix Issue 1399: make 'svn merge' gracefully warn the user when a chunk
of tree-delta can't be applied due to missing working-copy paths,
In other words, users should be able to apply any darn tree-delta
they want to their working copy, but it doesn't mean it will *all*
apply... some hunks will just be 'skipped', just as 'patch' behaves.
[There are still a few more edge-cases of 'svn merge' fragility
that need to be covered, look for those in upcoming commits.]
